## Express API Codebase Analysis - Complete Report

### 1. PROJECT STRUCTURE

```
/
├── src/
│   ├── app.ts              (Express app setup)
│   ├── server.ts           (Server entry point)
│   ├── db.ts               (In-memory database)
│   ├── types.ts            (TypeScript interfaces)
│   ├── middleware/
│   │   └── logger.ts       (Request logging middleware)
│   └── routes/
│       ├── posts.ts        (Posts routes)
│       └── comments.ts     (Comments routes)
├── tests/
│   ├── auth.test.ts        (Auth system tests)
│   ├── posts.test.ts       (Posts endpoint tests)
│   └── comments.test.ts    (Comments endpoint tests)
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
└── package-lock.json
```

### 2. MAIN APP & SERVER ENTRY POINT

**File: `/src/server.ts`**
- Entry point that starts the Express server
- Listens on `process.env.PORT` or defaults to port 3000
- Exports the app for testing

**File: `/src/app.ts`**
- Sets up Express application
- **Middleware:**
  - `express.json()` - JSON body parser
  - Custom `logger` middleware - logs all requests with method, path, status, duration
- **Route mounting:**
  - `POST /posts` routes via `postsRouter`
  - Comments routes via `commentsRouter`
- **Health check:** `GET /health` returns `{ status: "ok" }`

### 3. ROUTE FILES - ALL ENDPOINTS

#### **Posts Routes** (`/src/routes/posts.ts`)

| Method | Endpoint | Handler | Status Codes | Notes |
|--------|----------|---------|--------------|-------|
| GET | `/posts` | Returns all posts array | 200 | Public, no auth |
| GET | `/posts/:id` | Returns single post by ID | 200, 404 | Public, no auth |
| POST | `/posts` | Creates new post | 201, 400 | Requires `title`, `content`, optional `userId` (defaults to 1) |
| PUT | `/posts/:id` | Updates post title/content | 200, 404 | Partial update - only updates provided fields |
| DELETE | `/posts/:id` | Deletes post | 200, 404 | Returns deleted post object |

**Post Handler Details:**
- GET / (list all posts):
  ```typescript
  router.get("/", (req, res) => {
    res.json(posts);
  });
  ```
- GET /:id (single post):
  ```typescript
  router.get("/:id", (req, res) => {
    const id = parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
    const post = posts.find((p) => p.id === id);
    if (!post) {
      res.status(404).json({ error: "Post not found" });
      return;
    }
    res.json(post);
  });
  ```
- POST / (create post):
  ```typescript
  router.post("/", (req, res) => {
    const { title, content, userId } = req.body;
    if (!title || !content) {
      res.status(400).json({ error: "title and content are required" });
      return;
    }
    const newPost: Post = {
      id: nextId(posts),
      title,
      content,
      userId: userId || 1,
      createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),
    };
    posts.push(newPost);
    res.status(201).json(newPost);
  });
  ```
- PUT /:id (update post):
  ```typescript
  router.put("/:id", (req, res) => {
    const id = parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
    const index = posts.findIndex((p) => p.id === id);
    if (index === -1) {
      res.status(404).json({ error: "Post not found" });
      return;
    }
    const { title, content } = req.body;
    if (title) posts[index].title = title;
    if (content) posts[index].content = content;
    res.json(posts[index]);
  });
  ```
- DELETE /:id (delete post):
  ```typescript
  router.delete("/:id", (req, res) => {
    const id = parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
    const index = posts.findIndex((p) => p.id === id);
    if (index === -1) {
      res.status(404).json({ error: "Post not found" });
      return;
    }
    const deleted = posts.splice(index, 1);
    res.json(deleted[0]);
  });
  ```

#### **Comments Routes** (`/src/routes/comments.ts`)

| Method | Endpoint | Handler | Status Codes | Notes |
|--------|----------|---------|--------------|-------|
| GET | `/posts/:postId/comments` | List comments for post | 200, 404 | Public, filters by postId |
| GET | `/comments/:id` | Get single comment | 200, 404 | Public, no auth |
| POST | `/posts/:postId/comments` | Create comment on post | 201, 400, 404 | Requires `body`, optional `userId` (defaults to 1) |
| PUT | `/comments/:id` | Update comment | 200, 404 | Partial update - only updates `body` field |
| DELETE | `/comments/:id` | Delete comment | 200, 404 | Returns deleted comment object |

**Comment Handler Details:**
- GET /posts/:postId/comments (list for post):
  ```typescript
  router.get("/posts/:postId/comments", (req, res) => {
    const postId = parseInt(req.params.postId, 10);
    const post = posts.find((p) => p.id === postId);
    if (!post) {
      res.status(404).json({ error: "Post not found" });
      return;
    }
    const postComments = comments.filter((c) => c.postId === postId);
    res.json(postComments);
  });
  ```
- GET /comments/:id (single comment):
  ```typescript
  router.get("/comments/:id", (req, res) => {
    const id = parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
    const comment = comments.find((c) => c.id === id);
    if (!comment) {
      res.status(404).json({ error: "Comment not found" });
      return;
    }
    res.json(comment);
  });
  ```
- POST /posts/:postId/comments (create comment):
  ```typescript
  router.post("/posts/:postId/comments", (req, res) => {
    const postId = parseInt(req.params.postId, 10);
    const post = posts.find((p) => p.id === postId);
    if (!post) {
      res.status(404).json({ error: "Post not found" });
      return;
    }
    const { body, userId } = req.body;
    if (!body) {
      res.status(400).json({ error: "body is required" });
      return;
    }
    const newComment: Comment = {
      id: nextId(comments),
      postId,
      userId: userId || 1,
      body,
      createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),
    };
    comments.push(newComment);
    res.status(201).json(newComment);
  });
  ```
- PUT /comments/:id (update comment):
  ```typescript
  router.put("/comments/:id", (req, res) => {
    const id = parseInt(req.params.id, 10);
    const index = comments.findIndex((c) => c.id === id);
    if (index === -1) {
      res.status(404).json({ error: "Comment not found" });
      return;
    }
    const { body } = req.body;
    if (body) comments[index].body = body;
    res.json(comments[index]);
  });
